# Project Template persistence

**Project Template** (`isTemplate` / name `Project Template`) is the canonical board template that new projects and tests follow.

## Rules for agents

1. **Never wipe or reset Project Template content** unless the user explicitly asks to reset the template.
2. Do not run `resetTemplateToEmptyBoards`, demo seed injectors, or store restores that drop template tasks/groups without an explicit user request and a backup first.
3. Prefer fixing display/column bugs without rewriting `tasks` / `taskGroups` for the template project.
4. When changing persist/hydrate (`durableStoreStorage`, `devStoreSyncStorage`, Zustand persist), verify template Detailers (and other boards) still round-trip after reload.
5. Anything the user types on Project Template (titles, materials, dates, groups, statuses) must remain after HMR, app restart, and agent code edits.

## Template purpose

This template is what “everything needs to follow,” including test projects. Treat edits there as production data.
